    <description>Plants vinelike, clambering. Roots mostly aerial, but also in soil. Stems light
        green, 200–400 × 1–2 cm; ribs 4–6, acute; areoles 1.5–2.5 cm apart along ribs. Spines 7–8,
        yellow to blackish, conic, to 1 mm (rarely longer); radial spines 6–7, circular in cross
        section, hairlike spines absent; central spines 1. Flowers 12–14 × 7–8.5 cm; outer tepals
        narrow, oblong; inner tepals white to pink, narrowly oblong; areoles of ovary and flower
        tube spiny; scales and long hairs absent. Fruits not observed. 2n = 22.</description>
